import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='lon', y='lat', hue='state', palette='tab20', legend=False)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude across the US state capitals?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts().reset_index()
    state_counts.columns = ['state', 'count']
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='count', data=state_counts)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('Which state has the highest number of state capitals?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Number of State Capitals')
    max_state = state_counts.loc[state_counts['count'].idxmax()]
    plt.axhline(max_state['count'], color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {max_state['state']} ({max_state['count']:.2f})")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the average vowel count
    avg_vowel_count = data['vowel_count'].mean()

    # Create a histogram of vowel count
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='vowel_count', bins=5, color='blue', alpha=0.7)

    # Add a vertical line for the average vowel count
    plt.axvline(avg_vowel_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_vowel_count:.2f}')

    # Set the title and legend
    plt.title('What is the average vowel count of state capitals?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.boxplot(x='first_letter', y='vowel_count', data=data)
    plt.title("What is the relationship between the first letter of the state capital and its vowel count?", wrap=True)
    chart.legend(title='First Letter', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_filtered = data[data['vowel_count'] == 4]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data_filtered, x='lon', y='lat', hue='state', palette='tab20', s=100)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude for state capitals with a vowel count of 4?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left', borderaxespad=0)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
